title: SaxaVord Spaceport to host HyImpulse orbital rocket launches
summary: The UK’s SaxaVord Spaceport plans host orbital launches of HyImpulse Technologies rockets from late 2025.

title: European launch deal praised despite competition questions
summary: European governments and launch companies hailed an agreement reached last week on the future of the continent’s launch industry despite questions about how one aspect of that agreement, a competition, will work.

title: HyImpulse Ditch SaxaVord in Favour of Australia for Maiden Flight
summary:
German launch startup HyImpulse Technologies has announced that it will launch the maiden flight of its suborbital SR75 launch vehicle from the Southern Launch Koonibba Test Range in Australia. title: Telesat taps Aalyria to provide network orchestration

title: ESA Signs Starlab Commercial Space Station Agreement With Airbus and Voyager Space
summary: The European Space Agency has inked a memorandum of understanding with Airbus and Voyager Space to explore the potential of a Starlab commercial space station as a successor to the ISS.

title: Spire launches constellation management platform
summary: Spire Global, a space-based data and services firm, has launched a web-based app designed to simplify satellite constellation operations for its customers.

title: Bulgaria Signs The Artemis Accords
summary: Bulgaria is the 32nd country to officially joined the U.S.-led Artemis Accords, marking its commitment to principles for cooperative space exploration.
